Statistical Software and Methods:
• SPSS 28.0 for primary statistical analysis
• Microsoft Excel for data management and preliminary coding
• R Studio for advanced statistical modeling (if required)

Analysis Techniques:
Descriptive Analysis:
• Frequency distributions and cross-tabulations
• Measures of central tendency (mean, median, mode)
• Variability measures (standard deviation, variance)

Inferential Analysis:
• Chi-square test for association between categorical variables
• Independent t-test for comparing means between EV and petrol vehicle preferences
• One-way ANOVA for comparing preferences across multiple demographic groups
• Multiple regression analysis to identify predictive factors
• Factor analysis for grouping related preference variables
• Reliability analysis (Cronbach's Alpha) for scale validation

Significance Level: p < 0.05 for all statistical tests
